{
  "text": "However, Rundle et al. [CITATION_1] found early up-regulation of TGF-\uf062 and VEGF, consistent with previous fracture studies; which was an important result of our in vitro model in addition to the up-regulation of integrins. The traditional markers of osteoblastic differentiation (i.e., collagen type I, alkaline phosphatase and osteocalcin) were not up-regulated. The signaling PTH and BMP pathways were not up-regulated, which could indicate that 24 hours is too short culture period. Or the cultured cells need other stimuli to up-regulate genes necessary for later osteoblastic differentiation.",
